25. pascebant: takes here its more usual cons. as in Verg. G. 3, 143; 4, 181, etc. See 2, 3, 42 n. Note the succession of picturesque imperfecte in this passage (25-34).— Palatia: 1, 1, 4 11. The plural is due to the exigencies of metre. The singular is possible only when the final syllable can be elided before a short vowel (in this period generally undesirable). Even in the plural the genitive, dative, and ablative (Palatiorum, Palatiis) are quite im- possible. So of Capitolia and of all other nouns of the first and second de· clensions in which the final syllable is preceded by a trochee.
